This paper is about an object detection algorithm that improves the accuracy of detecting small objects by incorporating context information. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the relationship between effective receptive fields and theoretical receptive fields, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its algorithm on the MS-COCO dataset, which is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
